Name: AccountCurrencyCode
Notes: The currency of the Customer account.

Name: AccountDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer account.

Name: AccountTimeZoneId
Notes: Name of the timezone selected for the Customer account. For example: "(GMT-05:00) Eastern Time". This field does not reflect the current state of daylight saving time for the timezone.

Name: ActiveViewCpm
Notes: Average cost of viewable impressions (ActiveViewImpressions).

Name: ActiveViewCtr
Notes: How often people clicked your ad after it became viewable. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ActiveViewImpressions
Notes: How often your ad has become viewable on a Display Network site.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurability
Notes: The ratio of impressions that could be measured by Active View over the number of served impressions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurableCost
Notes: The cost of the impressions you received that were measurable by Active View.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurableImpressions
Notes: The number of times your ads are appearing on placements in positions where they can be seen.

Name: ActiveViewViewability
Display Name: Active View viewable impr. / measurable impr.
Notes: The percentage of time when your ad appeared on an Active View enabled site (measurable impressions) and was viewable (viewable impressions). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AdGroupAdDisapprovalReasons
Notes:
List of disapproval reasons for the ad.
Starting with v201509, list elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: AdGroupAdTrademarkDisapproved
Notes: Indicates if the ad is disapproved because of trademark policy issues.

Name: AdGroupId
Notes: The ID of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupName
Notes: The name of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: Status of the ad group.

Name: AdNetworkType1
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Search Network
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
Notes: First level network type.

Name: AdNetworkType2
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Google search
SEARCH_PARTNERS / Search partners
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
Notes: Second level network type (includes search partners).

Name: AdType
Enum Values:
DEPRECATED_AD / Other
IMAGE_AD / Image ad
PRODUCT_AD / Shopping ad
TEMPLATE_AD / Display ad
TEXT_AD / Text ad
THIRD_PARTY_REDIRECT_AD / Third party ad
DYNAMIC_SEARCH_AD / Dynamic search ad
CALL_ONLY_AD / Call only ad
EXPANDED_TEXT_AD / Expanded text ad
RESPONSIVE_DISPLAY_AD / Responsive display ad
UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes: The type of the Ad. Starting with v201605, if the ad's type is not supported in the report request's API version, this field will have the value "unknown".

Name: AdvertiserExperimentSegmentationBin
Enum Values:
OUTSIDE_OF_EXPERIMENT / outside experiment
CONTROL / control
EXPERIMENT / experiment
Notes: Experiment group of the impressions.

Name: AllConversionRate
Notes: AllConversions divided by total clicks that can be conversion-tracked. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AllConversions
Notes: Best estimate of the total number of conversions that AdWords drives. Includes website, cross-device, and phone call conversions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AllConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all of your conversions, including those that are estimated. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AverageCost
Notes: The average amount you pay per interaction. This amount is the total cost of your ads divided by the total number of interactions.

Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AverageCpe
Notes: The average amount that you’ve been charged for an ad engagement. This amount is the total cost of all ad engagements divided by the total number of ad engagements. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AverageCpm
Notes: Average Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).

Name: AverageCpv
Notes: The average amount you pay each time someone views your ad. The average CPV is defined by the total cost of all ad views divided by the number of views. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AveragePageviews
Notes: Average number of pages viewed per session. Imported from Google Analytics. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AveragePosition
Notes: Your ad's position relative to those of other advertisers. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AverageTimeOnSite
Notes: Total duration of all sessions (in seconds) / number of sessions. Imported from Google Analytics. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: BaseAdGroupId
Notes: The ID of base ad group of trial ad groups. For regular ad groups, this is equal to AdGroupId.

Name: BaseCampaignId
Notes: The ID of base campaign of trial campaigns. For regular campaigns, this is equal to CampaignId.

Name: BounceRate
Notes: Percentage of clicks where the user only visited a single page on your site, formatted as "x.xx%". Imported from Google Analytics. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: BusinessName
Notes: The business name in a reponsive display ad.

Name: CampaignId
Notes: The ID of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignName
Notes: The name of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
REMOVED / removed
Notes: The status of the Campaign.

Name: ClickAssistedConversions
Notes: The total number of conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign contributed one or more assist clicks.

Name: ClickAssistedConversionsOverLastClickConversions
Display Name: Click Assisted Conv. / Last Click Conv.
Notes: The total number of conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign received assist clicks divided by the total number of conversions for which it triggered the last click. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ClickAssistedConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all conversions for which this keyword, ad, ad group, or campaign triggered assist clicks. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ClickConversionRate
Notes: The number of converted clicks divided by your total clicks that can be tracked to a conversion. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ClickConversionRateSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ClickConversionRate.

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

Name: ClickSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in Clicks.

Name: ClickType
Enum Values:
URL_CLICKS / Headline
CALLS / Phone calls
OTHER / Other
PRODUCT_EXTENSION_CLICKS / Product plusbox offer
SITELINKS / Sitelink
PRODUCT_LISTING_AD_CLICKS / Shopping ad - Standard
GET_DIRECTIONS / Driving direction
OFFER_PRINTS / Print offer
BREADCRUMBS / Breadcrumbs
CALL_TRACKING / Manually dialed phone calls
MOBILE_CALL_TRACKING / Mobile phone calls
LOCATION_EXPANSION / Get location details
STORE_LOCATOR / Show nearby locations
TABLE_EXTENSION / Table Extension
VIDEO_WEBSITE_CLICKS / Website
VIDEO_CALL_TO_ACTION_CLICKS / Call-to-Action overlay
VIDEO_APP_STORE_CLICKS / App store
VIDEO_CARD_ACTION_HEADLINE_CLICKS / Cards
VIDEO_END_CAP_CLICKS / End cap
CLICK_ON_ENGAGEMENT_AD / Click on engagement ad
LOCATION_FORMAT_MAP / Map
LOCATION_FORMAT_LANDING_PAGE / Go to landing page
LOCATION_FORMAT_STORE_INFO / Go to store info
LOCATION_FORMAT_DIRECTIONS / Directions
LOCATION_FORMAT_CALL / Call
LOCATION_FORMAT_TEXT / Text
LOCATION_FORMAT_IMAGE / Image(s)
BROADBAND_PLAN / Broadband Plan
UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes: The Impressions field will reflect how often the ad was served with that click type available. Since ads can serve with multiple click types displayed, impressions may be double counted and the totals may not be accurate.

Name: ConversionCategoryName
Notes: A category that describes the action the user will take to complete a conversion. Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned. Values: "Download", "Lead", "Purchase/Sale", "Signup", "View of a key page", and "Other".

Name: ConversionRate
Notes: The number of conversions divided by total clicks that can be tracked to conversions. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Conversions
Notes: The number of conversions for all conversion actions that you have opted into optimization. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ConversionTrackerId
Notes: ID of the conversion tracker.

Name: ConversionTypeName
Notes: The name of the conversion type. Prevents zero-conversion rows from being returned.

Name: ConversionValue
Notes: The sum of conversion values for all conversions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ConvertedClicks
Notes: The number of clicks that converted within your chosen conversion window.

Name: ConvertedClicksSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ConvertedClicks.

Name: Cost
Notes: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period.

Name: CostPerAllConversion
Notes: Total cost divided by all conversions.

Name: CostPerConversion
Notes: Total cost divided by total ConversionValue.

Name: CostPerConvertedClick
Notes: Cost divided by your total converted clicks.

Name: CostPerConvertedClickSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CostPerConvertedClick.

Name: CostSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in Cost.

Name: CpcSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CPC.

Name: CpmSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CPM.

Name: CreativeApprovalStatus
Enum Values:
APPROVED / approved
FAMILY_SAFE / approved
NON_FAMILY_SAFE / approved (non family)
PORN / approved (adult)
UNCHECKED / pending review
DISAPPROVED / disapproved
Notes: Approval status of the ad.

Name: CreativeDestinationUrl
Notes: Destination URL of the ad.

Name: CreativeFinalAppUrls
Notes:
List of final app URLs of the ad. List entries will start with one of: a) "android-app:" (for Android apps) or b) "os-app:" (for iOS apps).
Starting with v201509, list elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: CreativeFinalMobileUrls
Notes:
List of final mobile URLs of the ad.
Starting with v201509, list elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: CreativeFinalUrls
Notes:
List of final URLs of the ad.
Starting with v201509, list elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: CreativeTrackingUrlTemplate
Notes: Tracking template of the ad.

Name: CreativeUrlCustomParameters
Notes:
List of custom parameters of the ad.
Starting with v201509, CustomParameters elements are returned in JSON map format.

Name: CriterionId
Notes: The Criterion ID.

Name: CriterionType
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
AD_SCHEDULE / Ad Schedule
AGE_RANGE / Age
APP_PAYMENT_MODEL / App Payment Model
CARRIER / Carrier
CONTENT_LABEL / Content Label
CUSTOM_AFFINITY / Custom Affinity
GENDER / Gender
LOCATION_GROUPS / Location Groups
IP_BLOCK / IP Block
KEYWORD / Keyword
LANGUAGE / Language
LOCATION / Location
MOBILE_APPLICATION / Mobile Application
MOBILE_APP_CATEGORY / Mobile App Category
MOBILE_DEVICE / Mobile Device
OPERATING_SYSTEM_VERSION / Operating System Version
PARENT / Parental status
PLACEMENT / Placement
PLATFORM / Platform
PREFERRED_CONTENT / Preferred Content
PRODUCT_PARTITION / Product Partition
PRODUCT_SCOPE / Product Scope
PROXIMITY / Proximity
USER_INTEREST / User Interest
USER_LIST / User List
VERTICAL / Vertical
WEBPAGE / Webpage
YOUTUBE_CHANNEL / YouTube Channel
YOUTUBE_VIDEO / YouTube Video
Notes: The type of criterion.

Name: CrossDeviceConversions
Notes: Conversions from when a customer clicks on an AdWords ad on one device, then converts on a different device or browser. Cross-device conversions are already included in your AllConversions column. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CtrSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in CTR.

Name: CustomerDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: DayOfWeek
Enum Values:
MONDAY / Monday
TUESDAY / Tuesday
WEDNESDAY / Wednesday
THURSDAY / Thursday
FRIDAY / Friday
SATURDAY / Saturday
SUNDAY / Sunday
Notes: The name of the day of the week, e.g., "Monday".

Name: Description
Notes: The descriptive text of an expanded text ad or responsive display ad.

Name: Description1
Notes: Line 1 description of the Ad.

Name: Description2
Notes: Line 2 description of the Ad.

Name: Device
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Other
DESKTOP / Computers
HIGH_END_MOBILE / Mobile devices with full browsers
TABLET / Tablets with full browsers
Notes: Device type where the impression was shown.

Name: DevicePreference
Notes: Platform ID of the device preference. You can look up the corresponding name and other information in the Platforms reference.

Name: DisplayUrl
Notes: Display URL of the Ad.

Name: EngagementRate
Notes: How often people engage with your ad after it's shown to them. This is the number of ad expansions divided by the number of times your ad is shown. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Engagements
Notes: The number of engagements. An engagement occurs when a viewer expands your Lightbox ad. Also, in the future, other ad types may support engagement metrics.

Name: ExternalCustomerId
Notes: The Customer ID.

Name: GmailForwards
Notes: The number of times your ad was forwarded to someone else as a message.

Name: GmailSaves
Notes: The number of times someone has saved your Gmail ad to their inbox as a message.

Name: GmailSecondaryClicks
Notes: The number of clicks to your landing page on the expanded state of Gmail ads.

Name: Headline
Notes: The ad headline for a TextAd. For other ad types such as TemplateAds, this field will contain a string representation of the key attributes of the ad.

Name: HeadlinePart1
Notes: The first part of an expanded text ad headline.

Name: HeadlinePart2
Notes: The second part of an expanded text ad headline.

Name: Id
Notes: ID of the main object of this row.

Name: ImageAdUrl
Notes: Prefix this value with "https://tpc.googlesyndication.com/pageadimg/imgad?id=" to get the full URL.

Name: ImageCreativeImageHeight
Notes: The height of the image ad. For other ad types, this will have no values.

Name: ImageCreativeImageWidth
Notes: The width of the image ad. For other ad types, this will have no values.

Name: ImageCreativeName
Notes: Name for the image ad.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversions
Notes: Total number of conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions prior to the last click.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversionsOverLastClickConversions
Display Name: Impr. Assisted Conv. / Last Click Conv.
Notes: Total number of conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions divided by the total number of conversions for which this object triggered the last click. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ImpressionAssistedConversionValue
Notes: Total value of all conversions for which this object triggered assist impressions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: ImpressionSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in Impressions.

Name: InteractionRate
Notes: How often people interact with your ad after it is shown to them. This is the number of interactions divided by the number of times your ad is shown. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Interactions
Notes: The number of interactions. An interaction is the main user action associated with an ad format—clicks for text and shopping ads, views for video ads, and so on.

Name: InteractionTypes
Notes: The types of interactions that are reflected in the Interactions, InteractionRate, and AverageCost columns.

Name: IsNegative
Notes: Indicates if the criterion for this row is a negative (exclusion) criterion.

Name: LabelIds
Notes:
List of label IDs for the main object of this row.
Starting with v201509, list elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: Labels
Notes:
List of label names for the main object of this row.
Starting with v201509, list elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: LongHeadline
Notes: The long format of the headline in a responsive display ad.

Name: Month
Notes: The first day of the month, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: MonthOfYear
Enum Values:
JANUARY / January
FEBRUARY / February
MARCH / March
APRIL / April
MAY / May
JUNE / June
JULY / July
AUGUST / August
SEPTEMBER / September
OCTOBER / October
NOVEMBER / November
DECEMBER / December
Notes: The name of the month of the year, e.g., "December".

Name: Path1
Notes: The text that appears in the ad with the displayed URL for an expanded text ad.

Name: Path2
Notes: In addition to "Path1", more text that appears in the ad with the displayed URL for an expanded text ad.

Name: PercentNewVisitors
Notes: Percentage of first-time sessions (from people who had never visited your site before), formatted as "x.xx%". Imported from Google Analytics. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: PositionSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ad position.

Name: PrimaryCompanyName
Notes: Company name of the account.

Name: Quarter
Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: ShortHeadline
Notes: The short format of the headline in a responsive display ad.

Name: Slot
Enum Values:
SearchRhs / Google search: Side
SearchTop / Google search: Top
SearchOther / Google search: Other
Content / Google Display Network
AfsTop / Search partners: Top
AfsOther / Search partners: Other
Unknown /
Notes: The position of the Ad.

Name: Status
Enum Values:
ENABLED / enabled
PAUSED / paused
DISABLED / disabled
Notes: The status of the main object in this row. For example, in a Campaign Performance Report this will be the status of each row's Campaign. In an Ad Group Performance Report this will be the status of each row's AdGroup.

Name: Trademarks
Notes:
Trademarks related to this object's approval status.
Starting with v201509, list elements are returned in JSON list format.

Name: ValuePerAllConversion
Notes: The value, on average, of all conversions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ValuePerConversion
Notes: The total value of your conversions divided by the total number of converted clicks. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ValuePerConvertedClick
Notes: The total value of all conversions divided by the total number of converted clicks. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoQuartile100Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched all of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoQuartile25Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 25% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoQuartile50Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 50% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoQuartile75Rate
Notes: Percentage of impressions where the viewer watched 75% of your video. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: VideoViewRate
Notes: The number of views your TrueView video ad receives divided by its number of impressions, including thumbnail impressions for TrueView in-display ads. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. Name: VideoViews
Notes: The number of times your video ads were viewed.

Name: ViewThroughConversions
Notes: The total number of view-through conversions. These happen when a customer sees an image or rich media ad, then later completes a conversion on your site without interacting with (e.g. clicking on) another ad.

Name: ViewThroughConversionsSignificance
Notes: Statistical significance of the experiment's change in ViewThroughConversions.

Name: Week
Notes: The date for the Monday of the week, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: Year
Notes: The year, formatted as yyyy.
